  "body": "### Description\n\nWe have a `@PersistenceUnitExtension` annotation to assign user-defined beans to the configuration of a persistence unit in Hibernate ORM.\r\n\r\nWe should add a similar annotation, say `@SearchExtension`, for Hibernate Search configuration.\r\n\r\nExamples:\r\n\r\n```\r\n@SearchExtension\r\npublic class MyAnalysisConfigurer extends ElasticsearchAnalysisConfigurer {\r\n    // ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n@SearchExtension(backend = \"someNamedBackend\")\r\npublic class MyAnalysisConfigurer extends ElasticsearchAnalysisConfigurer {\r\n    // ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nSame for other configuration properties accepting beans:\r\n\r\n* [quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.background-failure-handler](https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch#quarkus-hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch_quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.background-failure-handler)\r\n* [quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.elasticsearch.layout.strategy](https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch#quarkus-hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch_quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.elasticsearch.layout.strategy)\r\n* [quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.automatic-indexing.synchronization.strategy](https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch#quarkus-hibernate-search-orm-elasticsearch_quarkus.hibernate-search-orm.automatic-indexing.synchronization.strategy) (Maybe?)\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
